gaming pioneer benny binion who started out 
running illegal craps games and parlayed his fortunes to become 
owner of one of nevadas bigtime casinos has died he was 85 
binion died monday at valley hospital of a heartrelated 
condition according to a statement by henri bollinger public 
relations of los angeles he had a history of heart problems and 
entered the hospital several days ago for observation 
id asked the doctors in gamblers terms what were his odds 
and they told me six or eight to one against him said his son 
jack binion this morning i could see he wasnt going to make 
it 
he said his father who owned the horsehoe casino had been 
given the last rites of the roman catholic church on friday 
benny binion was born in grayson county texas to a family that 
sold race horses on the county fair circuit a connection that 
provided his entry into the gambling world 
he started out running illegal craps games usually out of hotel 
rooms 
the craps table would have legs that folded down and it fit 
into a crate that looked like a bed crate and since hotels always 
had beds going in or out if you had 30 minutes notice that you 
were going to be raided you could clean the place out he once 
recalled 
he was said to have killed two people in gunfights during those 
days but never went to prison for them with the charges dropped 
in each case he never apologized for them either once saying 
tough times make tough people 
he did serve time in prison for selling liquor during 
prohibition and for income tax evasion in the 1950s but toward the 
end of his life he had become such a friend of law enforcement that 
police officers borrowed money from his casino to make major 
undercover drug buys 
