<TEXT>
andrei d sakharov in the speech he was writing 
when he died said legislation allowing prosecutors to prolong 
maximum pretrial detention threatened society with a return to 
stalinist times a report said 
the respected weekly literaturnaya gazeta in its dec 27 
editions published a text of the speech that it said the nobel 
peace prize winner was working on when he collapsed and died in his 
study dec 14 
other soviet publications have said a text of the final speech 
of sakharov was circulated last weekend at the congress of peoples 
deputies where sakharov would have given the speech but they have 
not published it 
literaturnaya gazeta did not say how it obtained the text 
sakharov said that by trying to lengthen the amount of time 
soviets can be held before trial the procurator generals office 
was trying to free its hands entirely and return the country to 
the stormy times of illegality of the cult of personality 
stagnation and other rather gloomy periods 
the cult of personality is a reference to the rule of josef 
stalin during which prosecutors unencumbered by legal tradition or 
judicial oversight had all of stalins potential opponents and many 
other soviets imprisoned or killed 
the maximum length of time a suspect may be held has been nine 
months after which only the presidium of the supreme soviet could 
prolong detention 
the new law allows the deputy procurator general to extend such 
detention to one year and for the countrys top prosecutor to 
extend it to 18 months 
for decades prisoners in the soviet union have had no access to 
a lawyer during most of their pretrial detention 
soviet practice has been to allow the presence of a defense 
lawyer to prepare for trial only after the prosecutor has finished 
questioning the suspect and building his case 
this will not improve the results of the war with crime but 
only make our already sick society more cruel sakharovs text 
said the whole country will justly see a new lie in the new 
law 
sakharov cited the laws of many western countries limiting the 
amount of time suspects can be held without trial 
he criticized vice president anatoly i lukyanov for what he 
said were irregularities in conducting the supreme soviet 
legislative session nov 28 at which the new law was approved 
sakharov 68 was elected to the congress of peoples deputies 
in march and during the congress session earlier on dec 14 had 
spoken out in favor of declaring a group of reformminded deputies 
a political opposition to the communist party and government 
</TEXT>
