great balls of fire orion home video vhsbeta 8998 
rated pg13 
 
some of the best movie biographies are films such as lawrence 
of arabia gandhi and raging bull all carefully 
researched and written and based on a variety of sources 
and with such standardbearers why does hollywood continue to 
seek out books usually best sellers that give only a fragmented 
and sometimes biased account of an event or life and rush to 
make movies of them are the creative minds of the film industry 
incapable of doing original research and stories 
these questions come to mind with great balls of fire jim 
mcbrides movie on the life and times of the pianopumping rocker 
jerry lee lewis based on the book by myra lewis with murray 
silver mcbride and jack baran did the screenplay 
the movie is a kinetic romp through the early years of rock n 
roll when elvis was king and pretenders like jerry lee threatened 
to topple him the music is nonstop fun whether songs by presley 
and lewis or gene autry singing rudolph the red nosed reindeer 
or dave baby cortez stomping through happy organ 
dennis quaid is a treat as lewis hes manic lewd adorable and 
crazy he swaggers about with childish abandon and dances with the 
piano like a careless lover at times though quaid becomes almost 
cartoonish in his portrayal but thats ok because jerry lee lewis 
was a walking comic book 
myra winona ryder was jerry lees third wife she also was his 
third cousin and 13 years old when they married he was 22 
ryder heathers continues to impress with her film work 
she is a great casting choice for the pubescent pulchritudinous 
bubble gumchewing myra she is wideeyed and dreamyeyed giggly 
and pouty lusty and innocent 
their wedding scene is a wonderful slice of life ryder stares 
blankly at the justice of the peace mouth ajar like hes the 
purple people eater later at the dinner table with her parents 
she bursts into giggles knowing that shes married and they havent 
a clue 
the year was 1958 and lewis had already shot to the top of the 
charts with whole lotta shakin goin on and great balls of 
fire but his marriage to myra shocked a staid postwar public 
and lewis career crumbled 
the movie is centered on myra and jerry lees relationship it 
should have been titled jerry and myra and abruptly ends with 
the birth of their son steve allen who drowned in a swimming pool 
when he was 3 
the late trey wilson costars as sam phillips whose sun records 
launched presley and othersalec baldwin is deliciously 
selfrighteous as lewis cousin and boyhood buddy tv evangelist 
jimmy swaggart 
great balls of fire is a harmless piece of entertainment for 
a saturday afternoon its fun to watch especially quaids 
gymnastics and clownish grimaces 
but the movie lacks authenticity it seems to be laughing at 
itself and at the era it purports to chronicle theres also an 
element of racism a scene at a black nightspot for example 
depicts black patrons as lewd animals doing bumps and grinds and 
crawling over each other in the most suggestive ways 
by dolores barclay ap arts editor 
