<TEXT>
jeff brock has never recorded a hit 
song but people who watch tv frequently hear his music 
the 39yearold brock is president of a music house a 
company that provides tunes for tv commercials brock music his 
company has won or shared five clios or addys national awards for 
excellence in advertising 
some of his bestknown music accompanied these spots 
actor richard farnsworth posing in a desert eating chips with 
the tag line the flavors a legend 
fastfood hamburger containers open their lids and talk to 
each other 
a bleach with the hook line dont just get em clean get 
em vivid 
brock provides music to advertising agencies that have contracts 
with major corporations he comes up with original music or 
arranges a wellknown song that already has been chosen for an ad 
brock who supervises a staff of four plus several freelance 
music writers and arrangers says music is important to the overall 
content 
i think music plays an immense role in the memorability of a 
spot when you have 5yearold kids running around singing jingles 
all day you know it has a lot of impact on peoples minds he 
said 
he estimates that 70 percent of his work is post scores 
seeing the ad without music and writing a tune to emphasize whats 
happening visually 
the music is supposed to be poignant and jump out brock 
said 
the guidelines vary 
they will say they want something appealing to kids age 12 to 
young adults age 25 in that age group you go for something hard 
hitting something a little more rock n roll 
sometimes they say they want music like and they name the 
artist i come up with something similar to that artist or that 
style he said 
sometimes we go out on a limb and say we dont think it will 
work and heres what we suggest 
and in other cases they say they have no earthly idea what 
they want but they know it when they hear it those are the 
toughies you may come up with something you think is incredibly 
good but the client doesnt 
for a recent spot about food to be taken to work he was 
instructed to come up with music that sounded classical english 
very proper 
when i wrote those scores i wrote from an acoustical 
standpoint with strings and woodwinds and light fun 
britishsounding music it came out beautifully and they are airing 
nationally 
he writes some lyrics but most of the time they are written by 
the ad agency we sort of pick up the ball and run with it 
wherever they decide to pass it off to us brock said 
he always knows the client but sometimes it is top secret 
were not supposed to let out what were doing or the 
campaign and this can be painful because youve just done a 
wonderful session for someone and they are not going to break the 
campaign for three months and you cant even play it for anybody 
in most cases the spots are 30 seconds long some only 15 
seconds 
you dont get a chance to say much in 15 seconds he said 
the companies and products he has worked with include general 
mills century 21 k mart the walt disney co cbs news folgers 
mcdonalds long john silvers and ralston purina 
